Package corc.structure

Interface ICardset<C extends ICard>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - The subclass of ICard to be stored
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<C>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDeck<C>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Cardset, Deck
    public interface ICardset<C extends ICard>
extends java.lang.Iterable<C>
    An iterable list of Card objects.

    Subclasses CAN use a subclass of a Collection underneath, and is even recommended. However, a subclass of this SHOULD NOT directly inherit from a Collection. This is to enforce the API of "addCard(ICard)" instead of a Collection's version of "add(ICard)".

    To account for potential needs of treating this class as a Collection, a toCollection() has been included to the subclass to implement.

      • shuffle

        void shuffle()
        SHOULD randomly shuffle this. Such that the Cards stored by this would not appear in the same order as another Cardset after the sort() method is called on the other. Set logic: Cardset1.shuffle() != Cardset2.sort()

        This method SHOULD NOT shuffle the same pattern on each call. (e.x. SHOULD NOT always swap index 1 and 17). While there can be a possibility that two Cardsets result in the same order after this method, the chance should be unlikely. Set logic: Cardset1.shuffle() != Cardset2.shuffle()

      • sort

        void sort()
        SHOULD sort this in a consistent manner.

        Any number of calls to this method on the same Deck should produce the same ordering of Cards stored internally. Set logic: Cardset1.sort() == Cardset2.sort() Cardset1.sort() == Cardset1.sort()
